{
  "texts": [
    "Occluded P showed positive non-linear re-lationships with all those variables with exception of sand (Fig. S16).",
    "In our analysis, the reference soil group has very low values of MDA (Figs. 7 and S17), indicating that they are not powering the accuracy of the random forest models and, thus, are not good predictors for P forms in the soil in our statistical approach.",
    "The predicted values of total P in our map presented a correlation coefficient of 0.73 (p<0.01) when compared with the observed values in the fitting dataset.",
    "For comparison, the map of total P of He et al. (2021) presented a correlation coefficient of 0.36 (p<0.01).",
    "We used soil data sampled in 108 plots of the RAINFOR network in the pan-Amazon region (the fitting dataset) to train, test, and select random forest regression models."
  ]
}